What you need to know:

Hamilton moved on to 98 career wins after a surprise second change of tyres hoodwinked Red Bull to lift him 14 points clear of Verstappen in the drivers' standingsHamilton had set off from pole for the 100th time but was beaten to the first corner by Verstappen, with Leclerc dishing out the same treatment on Bottas on turn twoHamilton moved into second but there was no hint of team orders with Bottas forcing his teammate into full overtaking mode